            "<p><img src='https://img.shields.io/github/license/eProsima/Fast-RTPS.svg' alt='License' /> <img src='https://img.shields.io/github/release-date/eProsima/Fast-RTPS.svg' alt='' /> <img src='https://img.shields.io/github/commits-since/eProsima/Fast-RTPS/latest.svg' alt='' /></p> <p>eProsima Fast DDS is a C++ implementation of the RTPS (Real Time Publish Subscribe) protocol, which provides publisher-subscriber communications over unreliable transports such as UDP, as defined and maintained by the Object Management Group (OMG) consortium. Fast DDS provides both the <a href='https://www.omg.org/spec/DDS/1.4'>OMG DDS 1.4</a> and the <a href='https://www.omg.org/spec/DDSI-RTPS/2.2/'>OMG RTPS 2.2</a> interoperable wire-protocol standards.</p> <p>eProsima Fast DDS holds the benefit of being standalone and up-to-date, as most vendor solutions either implement RTPS as a tool to implement DDS or use past versions of the specification.</p>",
